There once lived a young lad named Jin Wang, who, after moving to a new land, longed to shed his very self to fit among his unfamiliar peers, wishing always to be seen as purely American. Far away, a mighty Monkey King, proud and powerful, yearned to be more human, battling the very heavens to escape his true form. And then there was Danny, a seemingly ordinary boy, whose every joy was shattered by the arrival of his truly dreadful cousin, Chin-Kee. Thus, these three disparate tales, each born of a yearning for acceptance and a struggle against true identity, began their separate journeys, only to discover their fates were strangely intertwined, leading all to a profound truth about belonging.
